fields.name: countOfColumns
fields.description: Null for transactional datasets

fields.name: fileFormat
fields.description: Not null for transactional datasets

fields.name: fileName
fields.description: The name of the file under which it is stored on the server

fields.name: numberOfUses
fields.description: Numbers of MainPrimitive type tasks

fields.name: originalFileName
fields.description: The original name of the file submitted by the user

fields.name: overview
fields.description:
Returns an overview of the statistics of the dataset columns:
number of columns, rows, number of categorical columns, number of columns of each type.

fields.name: state
fields.description: Returns null if statistics have not yet started to be calculated

fields.name: stats
fields.description: Returns an empty array if statistics have not yet been calculated

fields.name: hasTid
fields.description: For AR algorithm, when type = "TABULAR"

fields.name: inputFormat
fields.description: For AR algorithm

fields.name: itemColumnIndex
fields.description: For AR algorithm, when type = "SINGULAR"

fields.name: tidColumnIndex
fields.description: For AR algorithm, when type = "SINGULAR"

types.name: Float
types.description: The `Float` scalar type represents signed double-precision fractional values as specified by [IEEE 754](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_floating_point).

types.name: ID
types.description: The `ID` scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as `"4"`) or integer (such as `4`) input value will be accepted as an ID.

types.name: Int
types.description: The `Int` scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

fields.name: internalError
fields.description:
Admins with permission 'VIEW_ADMIN_INFO' can view errorMsg value.
Users without these rights will receive null

inputFields.name: pagination
inputFields.description: All deps. Can be null, but only for downloadResults mutation

inputFields.name: type
inputFields.description: AR, FD, CFD, MFD, TypoFD, Stats

inputFields.name: radius
inputFields.description: TypoCluster (>=0, if undefined, then use defaultRadius)

inputFields.name: ratio
inputFields.description: TypoCluster (0..1, if undefined, then use defaultRatio)

inputFields.name: typoFD
inputFields.description: TypoCluster (string, which represents FD. For example string [0,1,3] represents FD: (0,1) -> 3)

fields.name: approveRecoveryCode
fields.description:
User mustn't be logged in. User must send code.
Then user must send query changePassword without current password hash.

fields.name: approveUserEmail
fields.description:
Code for email approving is temporary (24 hours, destroys after first attempt).
User must be logged in account and have account status Email Verification.
Returns new token pair.

fields.name: changePassword
fields.description:
This mutation can be used in two cases:
1) User logged in and wants to change his password.
He must send current and new password hashes.
Throws error if new pwd equal to previous or current pwd incorrect
2) User approved verification code for password recovery.
He must send hash for new password and email.

fields.name: changeTaskResultsPrivacy
fields.description:
By default, task's result is public. (Only authorized people can look results)
This query allows client to set task privacy.

fields.name: createFeedback
fields.description:
Creates feedback for user and saves information to the database.
Administrators (with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO") can see feedbacks

fields.name: createMainTaskWithDatasetChoosing
fields.description:
This query supports several restrictions:
1) Anonymous (with permission "USE_BUILTIN_DATASETS") can only choose built in dataset
2) Authorized user (with permission "USE_OWN_DATASETS") can also choose his uploaded datasets
3) Administrators (with permission "USE_USERS_DATASETS") can use all datasets
***
By default, the result of the algorithm is visible for all users.
forceCreate is irrelevant for stats algorithm

fields.name: createSpecificTask
fields.description:
Specific tasks are similar to creating MainTask.
But you don't need to upload/choose file.
Also if similar task was executed before, you will receive previous result.
When you create main task with dataset choosing you can change behaviour by changing
argument forceCreate.

fields.name: createUser
fields.description: After creating new account user will have anonymous permissions;

fields.name: deleteStatsInfo
fields.description:
Delete info about stats mining task.
All users can remove info about stats for built-in datasets.
All users can remove info about their tasks for their datasets.
Admins can remove info about all stats tasks.

fields.name: deleteTask
fields.description: Soft delete. Users can delete own tasks. Administrators can delete task of any user.

fields.name: downloadResults
fields.description:
This query allows users to download task results.
User can choose his own datasets (pass fileID).
Works only for FD, CFD and AR

fields.name: issueCodeForPasswordRecovery
fields.description:
User mustn't be logged in. After the request, a confirmation code
will be sent to the user's mail (code expires after 1h, dies after 1st use).
This code user should sent in mutation approveRecoveryCode.

fields.name: issueVerificationCode
fields.description:
This query issues (or reissues) new verification code.
Previous code will be destroyed.

fields.name: logIn
fields.description:
User can be logged in to multiple accounts at once.
Client must pass password hash in params (not password!).
If user's email wasn't approved, he will not be able to log in.

fields.name: logOut
fields.description:
If user wants to close all session, he must pass option allSession with value true.
By default, only current session will be closed.
If the request throws an error, then the user wasn't logged out of the account (session still valid)

fields.name: refresh
fields.description:
When user's access token expired, client must send request fir refreshToken.
If access token is already expired, you mustn't set header authorization with accessToken.
Otherwise you will see error with code 401.

fields.name: uploadDataset
fields.description:
This query allows authorized users upload datasets.
User can choose his own datasets (pass fileID) in query createMainTaskWithDatasetChoosing.

types.name: OverviewData
types.description:
If 'name' = Columns, 'amount' contains the number of columns in the dataset.
If 'name' = Rows, 'amount' contains the number of rows in the dataset.
If 'name' = Categorical, then 'amount' contains the number of categorical columns.
Otherwise, 'name' contains the column type, 'amount' contains the number of columns
with that type.

fields.name: datasetInfo
fields.description:
All user can see built in dataset
Authorized users can see their dataset
Users with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO" can see all dataset

fields.name: datasets
fields.description: Query for admins with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO"

fields.name: feedbacks
fields.description:
This query allows admin with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO" see users feedbacks
Throws an error if limit <= 0 or limit > 100 offset < 0

fields.name: getAnonymousPermissions
fields.description:
When user isn't authorized, he must get permissions for anonymous user.
If user logged in, he must extract permission from access token.
***
Tasks, created by anonymous, can't be private

fields.name: sessions
fields.description: Query for admins with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO"

fields.name: taskInfo
fields.description:
User can see results if one of the conditions is met:
1) Task was created by anonymous
2) Task was created by this user
3) Task isn't private
4) User has permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO"

fields.name: tasksInfo
fields.description: Query for admins with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO"

fields.name: users
fields.description: Query for admins with permission "VIEW_ADMIN_INFO"

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

fields.name: typoClusters
fields.description:
Only for preview. You must use field specificCluster to get
more info about specific cluster.

fields.name: defaultRadius
fields.description: Typo Miner (>=0)

fields.name: defaultRatio
fields.description: Typo Miner (0<= ratio <=1)

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

enumValues.name: QUERY
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a query operation.

enumValues.name: MUTATION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a mutation operation.

enumValues.name: SUBSCRIPTION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a subscription operation.

enumValues.name: FIELD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment definition.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_SPREAD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment spread.

enumValues.name: INLINE_FRAGMENT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an inline fragment.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a variable definition.

enumValues.name: SCHEMA
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a schema definition.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a scalar definition.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an object type definition.

enumValues.name: FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field definition.

enumValues.name: ARGUMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an argument definition.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an interface definition.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a union definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM_VALUE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum value definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object type definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object field definition.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByUrl`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

args.name: reason
args.description: Explains why this element was deprecated, usually also including a suggestion for how to access supported similar data. Formatted using the Markdown syntax, as specified by [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/).

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: specifiedBy
directives.description: Exposes a URL that specifies the behaviour of this scalar.

args.name: url
args.description: The URL that specifies the behaviour of this scalar.
